President Muhammadu Buhari is currently meeting with the service chiefs and heads of security agencies over the security challenges confronting the country. The meeting comes a day after the killing of a Catholic priest in Kaduna state. John Cheitnum, priest of the Kafanchan Catholic diocese, was found dead after he was abducted by gunmen on July 15 in Kaduna. The president had condemned the killing, saying his administration remains committed to ensuring improved security. The service chiefs present are Lucky Irabor, chief of defence staff; Faruk Yahaya, chief of army staff; Awwal Gambo, chief of air staff, and Isiaka Amao, chief of naval staff. Below are photos. <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-727001" src="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/20220721_112130.jpg" alt="" width="1500" height="1000" srcset="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/20220721_112130.jpg 1500w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/20220721_112130-300x200.jpg 300w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/20220721_112130-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/20220721_112130-768x512.jpg 768w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/20220721_112130-24x16.jpg 24w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/20220721_112130-36x24.jpg 36w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/20220721_112130-48x32.jpg 48w" sizes="(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px" /> <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-727002" src="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/20220721_112119.jpg" alt="" width="1500" height="1000" srcset="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/20220721_112119.jpg 1500w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/20220721_112119-300x200.jpg 300w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/20220721_112119-1024x683.jpg 10